The paper deals with RGBD salient object detection using a convolutional neural network (CNN) to learn the interaction mechanism between low-level saliency cues. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as feature extraction and image segmentation, which are commonly associated with the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the use of a CNN for learning and prediction suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), which are relevant to the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of superpixel-based Laplacian propagation, which is a technique for image processing and manipulation, and could be associated with the cs.MM sub-category. Finally, the use of a trained CNN suggests the possibility of using neural network optimization techniques, which are relevant to the cs.NE sub-category.
